}, "f89cb929-9e4b-4067-89fc-5534d4e99001": {"node_ids": ["4e224778-a072-4f70-8e65-04217c680604"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 11, "title": "A survey on deep learning for drug-target binding prediction: models, methods, and applications"}}, "5a346f7e-80f5-436e-afba-6a1579cdf267": {"node_ids": ["dc86ad6b-5078-4e07-814d-7d2cfa6ff467"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 12, "title": "MSN-DTA: a multi-scale node adaptive graph neural network for interpretable drug\u2013target binding affinity prediction"}}, "e776f9d0-d448-4eed-83f7-d24b7f3a9849": {"node_ids": ["a06830f2-cbb3-4556-ba77-b1dd5200652b"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 13, "title": "ICAN: Interpretable Cross-Attention Network for drug-target interaction prediction"}}, "d0e94130-7920-426a-85e3-f3dd670d1477": {"node_ids": ["b055748f-0d7f-4928-a53c-166989b7149d"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 14, "title": "AttentionSiteDTI: graph-based attention mechanism for protein binding site identification"}}, "6f750974-a867-4452-ac8f-2bd7296e8be5": {"node_ids": ["b3ca973d-74e9-412b-af8a-a62a0ac3bf53"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 15, "title": "BindingSiteAugmentedDTA: reducing search space of potential binding sites with interpretability"}}, "18adc0f5-85cc-4eea-a52f-bd1e374f92af": {"node_ids": ["f127e3e3-fc2e-451e-bbc5-ed1501d27a48"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 16, "title": "AffinityVAE: protein-ligand interaction feature map for interpretable affinity prediction"}}, "ed617669-d0e7-43ee-a6f3-374b175e3d6b": {"node_ids": ["78591b47-87e8-4cbb-b180-19d1996cdad8"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 17, "title": "Improving drug\u2013target affinity prediction by adaptive self-supervised learning"}}, "26452bdc-98ee-43f3-a470-a29a201f80de": {"node_ids": ["7ff5648f-846a-4f20-91b4-dc9194301670"], "metadata": {"paper_id": 18, "title": "DeepCDA: deep learning-based compound and protein interaction prediction with two-sided attention mechanism"}}}, "docstore/data": {"df0c6857-5401-4406-9907-0524d69fd108": {"__data__": {"id_": "df0c6857-5401-4406-9907-0524d69fd108", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"paper_id": 1, "title": "Deep Learning for Predicting Drug-Target Binding Affinity: A Comprehensive Review"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "a5a88fa8-e05d-46e5-917f-c2dcac5d8451", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"paper_id": 1, "title": "Deep Learning for Predicting Drug-Target Binding Affinity: A Comprehensive Review"}, "hash": "5138256af1cd02ca1e9081eaa2309f6baa0679ab331fcee7945ab8fc2ba4a0f9", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u6807\u9898: Deep Learning for Predicting Drug-Target Binding Affinity: A Comprehensive Review\n\u5173\u952e\u8bcd: \n\u6458\u8981: This paper provides a comprehensive review of deep learning approaches for predicting drug-target binding affinity (DTA), covering sequence-based methods (CNN, RNN, Transformer), structure-based methods (GNN, graph transformers), and complex-based models. It discusses datasets like Davis, KIBA, and BindingDB, evaluation metrics including MSE, CI, and r\u00b2, and analyzes the strengths and limitations of different AI architectures for DTA prediction.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 545, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "8b75971a-fc6c-4365-a301-cd40e8889277": {"__data__": {"id_": "8b75971a-fc6c-4365-a301-cd40e8889277", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"paper_id": 3, "title": "GraphDTA: predicting drug\u2013target binding affinity with graph neural networks"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "98369ca4-5a09-463f-a378-52afa59d9c52", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"paper_id": 3, "title": "GraphDTA: predicting drug\u2013target binding affinity with graph neural networks"}, "hash": "943248161b90891339cb306280d525620e1afc7bb8e3344681a36433b6fdfa8d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u6807\u9898: GraphDTA: predicting drug\u2013target binding affinity with graph neural networks\n\u5173\u952e\u8bcd: \n\u6458\u8981: The development of new drugs is costly, time consuming and often accompanied with safety issues. Drug repurposing can avoid the expensive and lengthy process of drug development by finding new uses for already approved drugs. In order to repurpose drugs effectively, it is useful to know which proteins are targeted by which drugs. Computational models that estimate the interaction strength of new drug\u2013target pairs have the potential to expedite drug repurposing. Several models have been proposed for this task. However, these models represent the drugs as strings, which is not a natural way to represent molecules. We propose a new model called GraphDTA that represents drugs as graphs and uses graph neural networks to predict drug\u2013target affinity. We show that graph neural networks not only predict drug\u2013target affinity better than non-deep learning models, but also outperform competing deep learning methods. Our results confirm that deep learning models are appropriate for drug\u2013target binding affinity prediction, and that representing drugs as graphs can lead to further improvements.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 1188, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "95622497-e43c-40cc-9157-8cd2ecddb3bd": {"__data__": {"id_": "95622497-e43c-40cc-9157-8cd2ecddb3bd", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"paper_id": 10, "title": "MONN: A Multi-objective Neural Network for Predicting Compound-Protein Interactions and Affinities"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e701589d-d38f-4164-8287-565fabe17cf0", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"paper_id": 10, "title": "MONN: A Multi-objective Neural Network for Predicting Compound-Protein Interactions and Affinities"}, "hash": "b87f182b7f4161874e014d8f7388e57762655e1e5abef44736734aa55dcb0217", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u6807\u9898: MONN: A Multi-objective Neural Network for Predicting Compound-Protein Interactions and Affinities\n\u5173\u952e\u8bcd: \n\u6458\u8981: \u5f00\u53d1\u4e86\u4e00\u4e2a\u591a\u76ee\u6807\u795e\u7ecf\u7f51\u7edcMONN\uff0c\u7528\u4e8e\u540c\u65f6\u5b66\u4e60\u5316\u5408\u7269\u4e0e\u86cb\u767d\u8d28\u4e4b\u95f4\u7684\u6210\u5bf9\u975e\u5171\u4ef7\u76f8\u4e92\u4f5c\u7528\u548c\u7ed3\u5408\u4eb2\u548c\u529b\u3002MONN\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u65e0\u7ed3\u6784\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u4ec5\u4ee5\u5316\u5408\u7269\u7684\u56fe\u8868\u793a\u548c\u86cb\u767d\u8d28\u7684\u4e00\u7ea7\u5e8f\u5217\u4f5c\u4e3a\u8f93\u5165\u3002\u4e0e\u4f9d\u8d56\u6ce8\u610f\u529b\u673a\u5236\u7684\u65b9\u6cd5\u4e0d\u540c\uff0cMONN\u4f7f\u7528\u72ec\u7acb\u7684\u6210\u5bf9\u76f8\u4e92\u4f5c\u7528\u9884\u6d4b\u6a21\u5757\u6765\u5b66\u4e60\u975e\u5171\u4ef7\u76f8\u4e92\u4f5c\u7528\uff0c\u5e76\u901a\u8fc7\u9884\u6d4b\u7684\u975e\u5171\u4ef7\u76f8\u4e92\u4f5c\u7528\u7ed3\u679c\u6765\u589e\u5f3a\u7ed3\u5408\u4eb2\u548c\u529b\u7684\u9884\u6d4b\u3002\u7814\u7a76\u8868\u660e\uff0c\u795e\u7ecf\u6ce8\u610f\u529b\u96be\u4ee5\u81ea\u52a8\u6355\u83b7\u5316\u5408\u7269\u4e0e\u86cb\u767d\u8d28\u4e4b\u95f4\u7684\u975e\u5171\u4ef7\u76f8\u4e92\u4f5c\u7528\uff0c\u800cMONN\u901a\u8fc7\u989d\u5916\u76d1\u7763\u4fe1\u606f\u6210\u529f\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e86\u8fd9\u4e00\u76ee\u6807\uff0c\u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86\u66f4\u6709\u610f\u4e49\u7684\u53ef\u89e3\u91ca\u6027\u3002", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 339, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4e224778-a072-4f70-8e65-04217c680604": {"__data__": {"id_": "4e224778-a072-4f70-8e65-04217c680604", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"paper_id": 11, "title": "A surve